Publish Android APK (Free, No Play Store)
Build release APK → ./gradlew assembleRelease
Sign it → Android Studio → Build → Generate Signed APK
Upload to Google Drive → share link (anyone with link)
Users: Settings → Install unknown apps → allow browser → open Drive link → download → install
⚠️ Each update = re-upload + reshare link manually

iOS Free (No Developer Account)
Option A — AltStore (easiest, no jailbreak)
User installs AltStore on their iPhone via Mac/PC
You share the .ipa file → user sideloads via AltStore
Limit: 3 apps max, re-sign every 7 days (free Apple ID limit)
Option B — Sideloadly — same 7-day limit, slightly easier install
Option C — TestFlight — needs $99/yr developer account (not free)
For real distribution iOS requires $99/yr. No way around it without jailbreak.

Stripe SDK integration note: Both Android and iOS have a clearly marked TODO comment where PaymentSheet should be invoked. Once the stripe-android / stripe-ios pods are added, replace the TODO with PaymentSheet.present(clientSecret) and on completion call viewModel.confirmTopUp(paymentIntentId).

